Bass '''David Thomas''' was a member of the [[choir of King's College, Cambridge]].  He has since become a well known [[early music]] / [[baroque music]] singer, who has won particular acclaim for his performances of works by [[Claudio Monteverdi|Monteverdi]], [[Henry Purcell|Purcell]], [[Johann Sebastian Bach|Bach]], [[George Frideric Handel|Handel]], and [[Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart|Mozart]].

Thomas is also a Professor of Singing at [[Trinity College of Music]] in London.

